BaiduTrans: 离子跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of an ion from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 质子跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of a proton from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 钾离子跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of potassium ions (K+) from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 钙离子跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of calcium (Ca) ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 镉离子跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of cadmium (Cd) ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 钴离子跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of cobalt (Co) ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 亚铁跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of ferrous iron (Fe(II) or Fe2+) ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 镁离子跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of magnesium (Mg) ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 无机阴离子跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of inorganic anions from one side of a membrane to the other. Inorganic anions are atoms or small molecules with a negative charge which do not contain carbon in covalent linkage.

BaiduTrans: 辉锑矿跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of antimonite from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 亚砷酸盐跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of arsenite from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 磷酸离子跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of phosphate (PO4 3-) ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 硫酸盐跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of sulfate ions, SO4(2-), from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 硫代硫酸盐跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of thiosulfate ions, S2O3(2-), from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 醋酸盐跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of acetate from one side of a membrane to the other. Acetate is the 2-carbon carboxylic acid ethanoic acid.

BaiduTrans: 尿囊酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of allantoate from one side of a membrane to the other. Allantoate is the end product of purine metabolism in mammals and some fish, formed form allantoin. It is widely distributed in plants as an important source of stored nitrogen.

BaiduTrans: 胆红素跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of bilirubin from one side of a membrane to the other. Bilirubin is a linear tetrapyrrole produced in the reticuloendothelial system from biliverdin and transported to the liver as a complex with serum albumin. In the liver, bilirubin is converted to bilirubin bisglucuronide, which is excreted in the bile.

BaiduTrans: 草酰乙酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of oxaloacetate, the anion of oxobutanedioic acid, from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 唾液酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of sialic acid from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 苹果酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of malate from one side of a membrane to the other. Malate is a chiral hydroxydicarboxylic acid, hydroxybutanedioic acid. The (+) enantiomer is an important intermediate in metabolism as a component of both the TCA cycle and the glyoxylate cycle.

BaiduTrans: 琥珀酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of succinate, the dianion of ethane dicarboxylic acid, from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 戊糖跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of a pentose sugar from one side of a membrane to the other. Pentose is a monosaccharide with 5 carbon atoms.

BaiduTrans: 己糖跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of a hexose sugar, a monosaccharide with 6 carbon atoms, from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 甘油跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of glycerol from one side of a membrane to the other. Glycerol is 1,2,3-propanetriol, a sweet, hygroscopic, viscous liquid, widely distributed in nature as a constituent of many lipids.

BaiduTrans: 甘油-3-磷酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of glycerol-3-phosphate from one side of a membrane to the other. Glycerol-3-phosphate is a phosphoric monoester of glycerol.

BaiduTrans: 氨基酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of amino acids from one side of a membrane to the other. Amino acids are organic molecules that contain an amino group and a carboxyl group.

description: aromatic amino acid transmembrane transporter activity
BaiduTrans: 芳香族氨基酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of aromatic amino acids from one side of a membrane to the other. Aromatic amino acids have an aromatic ring.

description: basic amino acid transmembrane transporter activity
BaiduTrans: 碱性氨基酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of basic amino acids from one side of a membrane to the other. Basic amino acids have side chains with a positive charge at pH 7.3.

description: neutral amino acid transmembrane transporter activity
BaiduTrans: 中性氨基酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of neutral amino acids from one side of a membrane to the other. Neutral amino acids have side chains with no charge at pH 7.3.

BaiduTrans: L-氨基酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of an L-amino acid from one side of a membrane to the other. L-amino acids are the L-enantiomers of amino acids.

BaiduTrans: L-天冬氨酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of L-aspartate from one side of a membrane to the other. L-aspartate is the anion derived from aspartic acid.

BaiduTrans: L-胱氨酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of L-cystine from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: L-谷氨酰胺跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of L-glutamine from one side of a membrane to the other. L-glutamine is 2-amino-4-carbamoylbutanoic acid.

BaiduTrans: 甘氨酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of glycine from one side of a membrane to the other. Glycine is aminoethanoic acid.

BaiduTrans: L-异亮氨酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of L-isoleucine from one side of a membrane to the other. L-isoleucine is (2R*,3R*)-2-amino-3-methylpentanoic acid.

BaiduTrans: 赖氨酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of L-lysine from one side of a membrane to the other. L-lysine is 2,6-diaminohexanoic acid.

BaiduTrans: L-甲硫氨酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of L-methionine from one side of a membrane to the other. L-methionine is 2-amino-4-(methylthio)butanoic acid.

BaiduTrans: L-脯氨酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of L-proline from one side of a membrane to the other. L-proline is pyrrolidine-2-carboxylic acid.

BaiduTrans: L-丝氨酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of L-serine from one side of a membrane to the other. L-serine is the L-enantiomer of 2-amino-3-hydroxypropanoic acid.

BaiduTrans: 多胺跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of polyamines, organic compounds containing two or more amino groups, from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 尿素跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of urea from one side of a membrane to the other. Urea is the water soluble compound H2N-CO-NH2.

BaiduTrans: 核碱跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of a nucleobase, any nitrogenous base that is a constituent of a nucleoside, nucleotide, or nucleic acidfrom one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 胞苷跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of cytidine, cytosine riboside, from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 尿苷跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of uridine, uracil riboside, from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 核苷酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of a nucleotide, any compound consisting of a nucleoside that is esterified with (ortho)phosphate, from one side of a membrane to the other.
Enables the transfer of ADP, adenosine diphosphate, from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 嘧啶核苷酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of a pyrimidine nucleotide, any compound consisting of a pyrimidine nucleoside esterified with (ortho)phosphate, from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 胆碱跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of choline from one side of a membrane to the other. Choline (2-hydroxyethyltrimethylammonium) is an amino alcohol that occurs widely in living organisms as a constituent of certain types of phospholipids and in the neurotransmitter acetylcholine.

BaiduTrans: 生物素跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of biotin from one side of a membrane to the other. Biotin is cis-tetrahydro-2-oxothieno(3,4-d)imidazoline-4-valeric acid; the (+) enantiomer is very widely distributed in cells and serves as a carrier in a number of enzymatic beta-carboxylation reactions.

BaiduTrans: 酰基肉毒碱跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of acyl carnitine from one side of a membrane to the other. Acyl carnitine is the condensation product of a carboxylic acid and carnitine and is the transport form for a fatty acid crossing the mitochondrial membrane.

Enables the transfer of coenzyme A from one side of a membrane to the other. Coenzyme A, 3'-phosphoadenosine-(5')diphospho(4')pantatheine, is an acyl carrier in many acylation and acyl-transfer reactions in which the intermediate is a thiol ester.

Enables the directed movement of flavin-adenine dinucleotide (FAD) from one side of a membrane to the other. FAD forms the coenzyme of the prosthetic group of various flavoprotein oxidoreductase enzymes, in which it functions as an electron acceptor by being reversibly converted to its reduced form.

BaiduTrans: 泛酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the directed movement of pantothenate across a membrane. Pantothenate is the anion of pantothenic acid, the amide of beta-alanine and pantoic acid; it is a B complex vitamin that is a constituent of coenzyme A and is distributed ubiquitously in foods.

BaiduTrans: 硫胺素跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of thiamine from one side of a membrane to the other. Thiamine is vitamin B1, a water soluble vitamin present in fresh vegetables and meats, especially liver.

BaiduTrans: 氟康唑跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of fluconazole from one side of a membrane to the other. Fluconazole is an antifungal drug used for oral candidiasis and cryptococcal meningitis; it is still under study for treatment of vaginal candidiasis and other fungal infections.

Enables the transfer of aminophospholipids from the exoplasmic to the cytosolic leaftlet of a membrane, using energy from the hydrolysis of ATP. Aminophospholipids contain phosphoric acid as a mono- or diester and an amino (NH2) group.
Enables the directed movement of sterols into, out of or within a cell, or between cells. Sterol are steroids with one or more hydroxyl groups and a hydrocarbon side-chain in the molecule.

Transport systems of this type enable facilitated diffusion of water (by an energy-independent process) by passage through a transmembrane aqueous pore or channel without evidence for a carrier-mediated mechanism.
Enables the facilitated diffusion of glycerol (by an energy-independent process) involving passage through a transmembrane aqueous pore or channel without evidence for a carrier-mediated mechanism.

Enables the energy-independent facilitated diffusion, mediated by passage of a solute through a transmembrane aqueous pore or channel. Stereospecificity is not exhibited but this transport may be specific for a particular molecular species or class of molecules.

Enables the transmembrane transfer of a potassium ion by an outwardly-rectifying voltage-gated channel. An outwardly rectifying current-voltage relation is one where at any given driving force the outward flow of K+ ions exceeds the inward flow for the opposite driving force.

BaiduTrans: 拉伸激活，阳离子选择性，钙通道活性
definition: Enables the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ion by a channel that opens in response to a mechanical stress in the form of stretching.

Enables the transfer of substances, sized less than 1000 Da, from one side of a membrane to the other. The transmembrane portions of porins consist exclusively of beta-strands which form a beta-barrel. They are found in the outer membranes of Gram-negative bacteria, mitochondria, plastids and possibly acid-fast Gram-positive bacteria.
Catalysis of the transport of a single molecular species across a membrane; transport is independent of the movement of any other molecular species.

Enables the active transport of a solute across a membrane by a mechanism whereby two or more species are transported together in the same direction in a tightly coupled process not directly linked to a form of energy other than chemiosmotic energy.
Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: solute(out) + H+(out) = solute(in) + H+(in).

Enables the active transport of a solute across a membrane by a mechanism whereby two or more species are transported in opposite directions in a tightly coupled process not directly linked to a form of energy other than chemiosmotic energy. The reaction is: solute A(out) + solute B(in) = solute A(in) + solute B(out).

BaiduTrans: 钠：无机磷酸盐转运体活性
definition: Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: Na+(out) + inorganic phosphate(out) = Na+(in) + inorganic phosphate(in).

BaiduTrans: 铁载体跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: siderophore-iron(out) + H+(out) = siderophore-iron(in) + H+(in).

BaiduTrans: 铁载体摄取跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: siderophore-iron(ferrioxamine)(out) + H+(out) = siderophore-iron(ferrioxamine)(in) + H+(in).

description: secondary active monocarboxylate transmembrane transporter activity
BaiduTrans: 次级活性单羧酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Catalysis of the movement of a monocarboxylate, any compound containing a single carboxyl group (COOH or COO-), by uniport, symport or antiport across a membrane by a carrier-mediated mechanism.
Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: Ca2+(in) + H+(out) = Ca2+(out) + H+(in).

BaiduTrans: 阳离子：氯离子转运体活性
definition: Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: cation(out) + Cl-(out) = cation(in) + Cl-(in).
Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: K+(out) + Cl-(out) = K+(in) + Cl-(in).
Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: Na+(out) + H+(in) = Na+(in) + H+(out).
Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: K+(in) + H+(out) = K+(out) + H+(in).
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + H2O + oligopeptide(out) = ADP + phosphate + oligopeptide(in).

BaiduTrans: ABC型谷胱甘肽S-缀合物转运蛋白活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + H2O + glutathione S-conjugate(in) -> ADP + phosphate + glutathione S-conjugate(out).
Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: ATP + H2O + Cd (cytosol) = ADP + phosphate + Cd (vacuole).

Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + H2O + peptide(in) = ADP + phosphate + peptide(out). Peptides exported include alpha-hemolysin, cyclolysin, colicin V and siderophores from Gram-negative bacteria, and bacteriocin, subtilin, competence factor and pediocin from Gram-positive bacteria.

Primary active carrier-mediated transport of a protein across a membrane, driven by the hydrolysis of the diphosphate bond of inorganic pyrophosphate, ATP, or another nucleoside triphosphate. The transport protein may or may not be transiently phosphorylated, but the substrate is not phosphorylated.
Binding to cholesterol (cholest-5-en-3-beta-ol); the principal sterol of vertebrates and the precursor of many steroids, including bile acids and steroid hormones.

BaiduTrans: 腐胺跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of putrescine from one side of a membrane to the other. Putrescine is 1,4-diaminobutane, the polyamine formed by decarboxylation of ornithine and the metabolic precursor of spermidine and spermine.

BaiduTrans: γ-氨基丁酸：质子转运体活性
definition: Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: gamma-aminobutyric acid(out) + H+(out) = gamma-aminobutyric acid(in) + H+(in).

BaiduTrans: 尿嘧啶：阳离子转运体活性
definition: Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: uracil(out) + cation(out) = uracil(in) + cation(in).

description: high-affinity secondary active nitrite transmembrane transporter activity
BaiduTrans: 高亲和力次级活性亚硝酸盐跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of nitrite from one side of the membrane to the other, up the solute's concentration gradient. The transporter binds the solute and undergoes a series of conformational changes. Transport works equally well in either direction and is driven by a chemiosmotic source of energy. In high affinity transport the transporter is able to bind the solute even if it is only present at very low concentrations.

BaiduTrans: 外排跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of a specific substance or related group of substances from the inside of the cell to the outside of the cell across a membrane.

BaiduTrans: 海藻糖跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of trehalose from one side of a membrane to the other. Trehalose is the disaccharide alpha-D-glucopyranosyl-alpha-D-glucopyranoside that acts of a reserve carbohydrate in certain fungi, algae and lichens.

BaiduTrans: 甘露糖跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of mannose from one side of a membrane to the other. Mannose is the aldohexose manno-hexose, the C-2 epimer of glucose. The D-(+)-form is widely distributed in mannans and hemicelluloses and is of major importance in the core oligosaccharide of N-linked oligosaccharides of glycoproteins.

BaiduTrans: 亚精胺跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of spermidine, N-(3-aminopropyl)-1,4-diaminobutane, from one side of a membrane to the other.
Generation of movement along a single- or double-stranded DNA molecule, driven by ATP hydrolysis.

BaiduTrans: 铁肠杆菌素跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of ferric-enterobactin from one side of a membrane to the other.
Binding to monomeric or multimeric forms of tubulin, including microtubules.

Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: ATP + H2O = ADP + phosphate, to directly drive the transport of ions across a membrane. The reaction is characterized by the transient formation of a high-energy aspartyl-phosphoryl-enzyme intermediate.

BaiduTrans: 乙醇跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of an alcohol from one side of a membrane to the other. An alcohol is any carbon compound that contains a hydroxyl group.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of glucosyl compounds, substances containing a group derived from a cyclic form of glucose or a glucose derivative.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of trehalose or a trehalose derivative.
Catalysis of the formation of L-glutamine and 2-oxoglutarate from L-glutamate, using NADH, NADPH or ferredoxin as hydrogen acceptors.
Catalysis of the reaction: hydrogen sulfide + acceptor + 3 H2O = sulfite + reduced acceptor.
Binding to cyclosporin A, a cyclic undecapeptide that contains several N-methylated and unusual amino acids.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 L-glutamate + NAD(+) = 2-oxoglutarate + L-glutamine + H(+) + NADH.

description: translation release factor activity, codon specific
BaiduTrans: 翻译释放因子活性，密码子特异性
definition: A translation release factor that is specific for one or more particular termination codons; acts at the ribosomal A-site and require polypeptidyl-tRNA at the P-site.

description: translation release factor activity, codon nonspecific
BaiduTrans: 翻译释放因子活性，密码子非特异性
definition: A translation release factor that is not specific to particular codons; binds to guanine nucleotides.
Catalysis of the reaction: NAD(+) + succinate = fumarate + H(+) + NADH.

BaiduTrans: 产生超氧化物的NAD（P）H氧化酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: NAD(P)H + O2 = NAD(P)H + O2-.
Binding to AMP, adenosine monophosphate.

Inhibition of the reactions brought about by dioxygen (O2) or peroxides. Usually the antioxidant is effective because it can itself be more easily oxidized than the substance protected. The term is often applied to components that can trap free radicals, thereby breaking the chain reaction that normally leads to extensive biological damage.

BaiduTrans: 犬尿氨酸-氧戊二酸转氨酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-kynurenine + 2-oxoglutarate = 4-(2-aminophenyl)-2,4-dioxobutanoate + L-glutamate.
Bonds to and modulates the activity of a channel. A channel catalyzes energy-independent facilitated diffusion, mediated by passage of a solute through a transmembrane aqueous pore or channel.

description: RNA polymerase II general transcription initiation factor activity
BaiduTrans: RNA聚合酶II一般转录起始因子活性
definition: A general transcription initiation factor activity that contributes to transcription start site selection and transcription initiation of genes transcribed by RNA polymerase II. The general transcription factors for RNA polymerase II include TFIIB, TFIID, TFIIE, TFIIF, TFIIH and TATA-binding protein (TBP). In most species, RNA polymerase II transcribes all messenger RNAs (mRNAs), most untranslated regulatory RNAs, the majority of the snoRNAs, four of the five snRNAs (U1, U2, U4, and U5), and other small noncoding RNAs. For some small RNAs there is variability between species as to whether it is transcribed by RNA polymerase II or RNA polymerase III. However there are also rare exceptions, such as Trypanosoma brucei, where RNA polymerase I transcribes certain mRNAs in addition to its normal role in rRNA transcription.

BaiduTrans: 蛋白质精氨酸N-甲基转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + (protein)-arginine = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + (protein)-N-methyl-arginine.

BaiduTrans: 蛋白质赖氨酸N-甲基转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a methyl group from S-adenosyl-L-methionine to the epsilon-amino group of a lysine residue in a protein substrate.

BaiduTrans: 甘油磷酸O-酰基转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: acyl-CoA + glycerone phosphate = 1-acylglycerone 3-phosphate + CoA.

BaiduTrans: 棕榈酰辅酶A水解酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: palmitoyl-CoA + H2O = CoA + palmitate.

BaiduTrans: 肉豆蔻酰-[酰基载体蛋白]水解酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: myristoyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + H2O = [acyl-carrier protein] + myristate.

BaiduTrans: 棕榈酰-[酰基载体蛋白]水解酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: palmitoyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + H2O = [acyl-carrier protein] + palmitate.

BaiduTrans: 酰基-[酰基载体蛋白]水解酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: acyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + H2O = [acyl-carrier protein] + a fatty acid.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a lipid or phospholipid.

BaiduTrans: tRNA（尿嘧啶）甲基转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a methyl group from a donor to a uracil residue in a tRNA molecule.
Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.
Catalysis of the reaction: 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol + ATP = a 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3-phosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).

BaiduTrans: 磷脂酰肌醇磷酸激酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + a phosphatidylinositol phosphate = ADP + a phosphatidylinositol bisphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4-phosphate + ATP = 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).

BaiduTrans: 磷脂酰肌醇-3,4,5-三磷酸-3-磷酸酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: phosphatidylinositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate + H2O = phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the transfer of an acetyl group to an acceptor molecule.
Catalysis of the transfer of a palmitoyl (CH3-[CH2]14-CO-) group to an acceptor molecule.
Catalysis of the transfer of an octanoyl (CH3-[CH2]6-CO-) group to an acceptor molecule.
Catalysis of the transfer of a malonyl group to a sulfur atom on the acceptor molecule.

BaiduTrans: tRNA（鸟嘌呤）甲基转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + tRNA = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + tRNA containing methylguanine.

BaiduTrans: tRNA（胞嘧啶-5-）甲基转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + tRNA = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + tRNA containing 5-methylcytosine.

BaiduTrans: tRNA（腺嘌呤-N1-）甲基转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + tRNA = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + tRNA containing N1-methyladenine.

BaiduTrans: 核糖核酸（腺嘌呤）甲基转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + rRNA = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + rRNA containing methyladenine.

BaiduTrans: rRNA（鸟嘌呤）甲基转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + rRNA = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + rRNA containing methylguanine.
Catalysis of the transfer of an acetyl group to a carbon atom on the acceptor molecule.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a pyrophosphate bond between two phosphate groups, leaving one phosphate on each of the two fragments.

Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction, a reversible chemical reaction in which the oxidation state of an atom or atoms within a molecule is altered. One substrate acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and becomes oxidized, while the other acts as hydrogen or electron acceptor and becomes reduced.
Binds to and increases the activity of a peptidase, any enzyme that catalyzes the hydrolysis peptide bonds.
Directly binding to and delivering copper ions to a target protein.

BaiduTrans: 超氧化物歧化酶铜伴侣活性
definition: A copper chaperone activity that specifically delivers copper to the Cu-Zn superoxide dismutase, to activate superoxide dismutase activity.

description: cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase regulator activity
BaiduTrans: 细胞周期素依赖性蛋白丝氨酸/苏氨酸激酶调节活性
definition: Modulates the activity of a cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase, enzymes of the protein kinase family that are regulated through association with cyclins and other proteins.
Binding to glycine, aminoethanoic acid.
Binding to an amino acid, organic acids containing one or more amino substituents.

BaiduTrans: 谷氨酰胺肽环转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-glutaminyl-peptide = 5-oxoprolyl-peptide + NH3.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH-OH group of donors
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于供体的CH-OH基团
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-OH group act as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a hydrogen or electron acceptor.
Catalysis of the reversible conversion of pyruvate or oxaloacetate to malate.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-OH group of donors, NAD or NADP as acceptor
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于供体的CH-OH基团，NAD或NADP作为受体
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-OH group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces NAD+ or NADP.

BaiduTrans: 羟基丙酮酸还原酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: D-glycerate + NADP+ = hydroxypyruvate + NADPH + H+.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors, NAD or NADP as acceptor
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于供体的醛或氧基，NAD或NADP作为受体
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which an aldehyde or ketone (oxo) group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces NAD or NADP.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors, disulfide as acceptor
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于供体的醛或氧基，二硫化物作为受体
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which an aldehyde or ketone (oxo) group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a disulfide.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-CH group of donors
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于供体的CH-CH组
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-CH group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a hydrogen or electron acceptor.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-CH group of donors, NAD or NADP as acceptor
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于供体的CH-CH基团，NAD或NADP作为受体
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-CH group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces NAD or NADP.

BaiduTrans: 烯醇基-[酰基载体蛋白]还原酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: acyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + NAD(P)+ = trans-2,3-dehydroacyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + NAD(P)H + H+.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH2 group of donors
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于供体的CH-NH2组
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-NH2 group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a hydrogen or electron acceptor.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH2 group of donors, NAD or NADP as acceptor
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于供体的CH-NH2组，NAD或NADP作为受体
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-NH2 group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces NAD+ or NADP.

BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于NAD（P）H
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which NADH or NADPH acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a hydrogen or electron acceptor.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on NAD(P)H, NAD(P) as acceptor
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于NAD（P）H，NAD（P）作为受体
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which NADH or NADPH acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces NAD+ or NADP.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on NAD(P)H, heme protein as acceptor
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于NAD（P）H，以血红素蛋白为受体
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which NADH or NADPH acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a heme protein.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on NAD(P)H, nitrogenous group as acceptor
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于NAD（P）H，含氮基团为受体
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which NADH or NADPH acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a nitrogenous group.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on a sulfur group of donors
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于供体的硫基团
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a sulfur-containing group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a hydrogen or electron acceptor.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on a sulfur group of donors, NAD(P) as acceptor
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于供体的硫基团，NAD（P）作为受体
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a sulfur-containing group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces NAD or NADP.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on a sulfur group of donors, oxygen as acceptor
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于供体的硫基团，氧作为受体
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a sulfur-containing group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces oxygen.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于成对供体，分子氧掺入或减少
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from each of two donors, and molecular oxygen is reduced or incorporated into a donor.

BaiduTrans: 2-氧戊二酸依赖性双加氧酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: A + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 = B + succinate + CO2. This is an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from 2-oxoglutarate and one other donor, and one atom of oxygen is incorporated into each donor.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, NAD(P)H as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于成对供体，分子氧掺入或还原，NAD（P）H作为一个供体，一个氧原子掺入
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from NADH or NADPH and one other donor, and one atom of oxygen is incorporated into one donor.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, reduced flavin or flavoprotein as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于成对供体，结合或还原分子氧，还原黄素或黄素蛋白作为一个供体，并结合一个氧原子
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from reduced flavin or flavoprotein and one other donor, and one atom of oxygen is incorporated into one donor.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with oxidation of a pair of donors resulting in the reduction of molecular oxygen to two molecules of water
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于成对供体，一对供体氧化导致分子氧还原为两个水分子
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from each of two donors, and molecular oxygen is reduced to two molecules of water.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on metal ions
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于金属离子
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction in which the oxidation state of metal ion is altered.

description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on iron-sulfur proteins as donors
BaiduTrans: 氧化还原酶活性，作用于铁硫蛋白作为供体
definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which an iron-sulfur protein acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a hydrogen or electron acceptor.

Catalysis of the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from one compound (generally regarded as the donor) to another compound (generally regarded as the acceptor). Transferase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 2.

BaiduTrans: 转移酶活性，转移一个碳基
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a one-carbon group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

BaiduTrans: 羧基或氨甲酰转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a carboxyl- or carbamoyl group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).
Catalysis of the transfer of an acyl group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

description: acyltransferase activity, transferring groups other than amino-acyl groups
BaiduTrans: 酰基转移酶活性，氨基酰基以外的转移基团
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of an acyl group, other than amino-acyl, from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).
Catalysis of the transfer of a glycosyl group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).
Catalysis of the transfer of a hexosyl group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).
Catalysis of the transfer of a pentosyl group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

description: transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups
BaiduTrans: 转移烷基或芳基（甲基除外）的转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of an alkyl or aryl (but not methyl) group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).
Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosylmethioninamine + spermidine = 5'-methylthioadenosine + spermine.

BaiduTrans: 转移酶活性，转移含磷基团
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

description: phosphotransferase activity, alcohol group as acceptor
BaiduTrans: 磷酸转移酶活性，醇基为受体
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to an alcohol group (acceptor).

description: phosphotransferase activity, phosphate group as acceptor
BaiduTrans: 磷酸转移酶活性，磷酸基作为受体
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to a phosphate group (acceptor).
Catalysis of the transfer of a nucleotidyl group to a reactant.

description: phosphotransferase activity, for other substituted phosphate groups
BaiduTrans: 其他取代磷酸基团的磷酸转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a substituted phosphate group, other than diphosphate or nucleotidyl residues, from one compound (donor) to a another (acceptor).
Catalysis of the transfer of sulfur atoms from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of various bonds, e.g. C-O, C-N, C-C, phosphoric anhydride bonds, etc. Hydrolase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 3.

description: hydrolase activity, acting on ester bonds
BaiduTrans: 水解酶活性，作用于酯键
definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any ester bond.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of phosphoric monoesters, releasing inorganic phosphate.

description: hydrolase activity, acting on glycosyl bonds
BaiduTrans: 水解酶活性，作用于糖基键
definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any glycosyl bond.

BaiduTrans: 水解酶活性，水解N-糖基化合物
definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any N-glycosyl bond.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a dipeptide.

BaiduTrans: 半胱氨酸型羧肽酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a single C-terminal amino acid residue from a polypeptide chain by a mechanism in which the sulfhydryl group of a cysteine residue at the active center acts as a nucleophile.

description: hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds
BaiduTrans: 水解酶活性，作用于碳氮（但不是肽键）
definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any carbon-nitrogen bond, C-N, with the exception of peptide bonds.

description: hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds, in linear amides
BaiduTrans: 线性酰胺中作用于碳氮（而非肽键）键的水解酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any non-peptide carbon-nitrogen bond in a linear amide.

description: hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds, in cyclic amides
BaiduTrans: 环酰胺中作用于碳氮键（而非肽键）的水解酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any non-peptide carbon-nitrogen bond in a cyclic amide.

description: hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds, in linear amidines
BaiduTrans: 水解酶活性，作用于线性酰胺中的碳氮（而非肽键）
definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any non-peptide carbon-nitrogen bond in a linear amidine, a compound of the form R-C(=NH)-NH2.

description: hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds, in cyclic amidines
BaiduTrans: 环脒中作用于碳氮（而非肽）键的水解酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any non-peptide carbon-nitrogen bond in a cyclic amidine, a compound of the form R-C(=NH)-NH2.

description: hydrolase activity, acting on acid anhydrides
BaiduTrans: 作用于酸酐的水解酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any acid anhydride.

description: hydrolase activity, acting on acid anhydrides, in phosphorus-containing anhydrides
BaiduTrans: 含磷酸酐中作用于酸酐的水解酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any acid anhydride which contains phosphorus.

Catalysis of the cleavage of C-C, C-O, C-N and other bonds by other means than by hydrolysis or oxidation, or conversely adding a group to a double bond. They differ from other enzymes in that two substrates are involved in one reaction direction, but only one in the other direction. When acting on the single substrate, a molecule is eliminated and this generates either a new double bond or a new ring.
Catalysis of the cleavage of C-C bonds by other means than by hydrolysis or oxidation, or conversely adding a group to a double bond.
Catalysis of the nonhydrolytic addition or removal of a carboxyl group to or from a compound.
Catalysis of the cleavage of a C-C bond in a molecule containing a hydroxyl group and a carbonyl group to form two smaller molecules, each being an aldehyde or a ketone.
Catalysis of the cleavage of a C-C bond by other means than by hydrolysis or oxidation, of a 3-hydroxy acid.
Catalysis of the cleavage of a carbon-oxygen bond by elimination of water.
Catalysis of the release of amides or amidines by the cleavage of a carbon-nitrogen bond or the reverse reaction with an amide or amidine as a substrate.
Catalysis of the release of amines by the cleavage of a carbon-nitrogen bond or the reverse reaction with an amine as a substrate.
Catalysis of the elimination of hydrogen sulfide or substituted H2S.
Catalysis of the geometric or structural changes within one molecule. Isomerase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 5.

description: racemase and epimerase activity, acting on carbohydrates and derivatives
BaiduTrans: 消旋酶和差向异构酶活性，作用于碳水化合物和衍生物
definition: Catalysis of a reaction that alters the configuration of one or more chiral centers in a carbohydrate molecule.
Catalysis of the transfer of a functional group from one position to another within a single molecule.

BaiduTrans: 分子内转移酶活性，磷酸转移酶
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group from one position to another within a single molecule.
The catalysis of certain rearrangements of a molecule to break or form a ring.
Catalysis of the joining of two molecules, or two groups within a single molecule, using the energy from the hydrolysis of ATP, a similar triphosphate, or a pH gradient.

BaiduTrans: 酸性氨（或酰胺）连接酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the ligation of an acid to ammonia (NH3) or an amide via a carbon-nitrogen bond, with the concomitant hydrolysis of the diphosphate bond in ATP or a similar triphosphate.
Catalysis of the ligation of an acid to an amino acid via a carbon-nitrogen bond, with the concomitant hydrolysis of the diphosphate bond in ATP or a similar triphosphate.

description: carbon-nitrogen ligase activity, with glutamine as amido-N-donor
BaiduTrans: 以谷氨酰胺为氨基供体的碳氮连接酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of the amide nitrogen of glutamine to a substrate. Usually composed of two subunits or domains, one that first hydrolyzes glutamine, and then transfers the resulting ammonia to the second subunit (or domain), where it acts as a source of nitrogen.

Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + H2O = ADP + H+ Pi. ATP hydrolysis is used in some reactions as an energy source, for example to catalyze a reaction or drive transport against a concentration gradient.

BaiduTrans: 甾醇3-β-葡萄糖基转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-glucose + a sterol = UDP + an O-glucosylsterol.
An thiol-dependent isopeptidase activity that cleaves SUMO from a target protein to which it is conjugated.
Catalysis of the reaction: H(2)O + 2 ferricytochrome c + nitrous oxide = 2 H(+) + 2 ferrocytochrome c + 2 nitric oxide.

BaiduTrans: 黄素连接巯基氧化酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the formation of disulfide bridges in proteins using FAD as the electron acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction: 4 R'C(R)SH + O2 = 2 R'C(R)S-S(R)CR' + 2 H2O2.

Catalysis of the lipoylation of a protein in two steps: ATP + (R)-lipoate + a [lipoyl-carrier protein]-L-lysine = a [lipoyl-carrier protein]-N6-(lipoyl)lysine + AMP + diphosphate (overall reaction): (1) ATP + (R)-lipoate = lipoyl-AMP + diphosphate; (2) lipoyl-AMP + a [lipoyl-carrier protein]-L-lysine = a [lipoyl-carrier protein]-N6-(lipoyl)lysine + AMP.
Catalysis of the reaction: protein N6-(octanoyl)lysine + 2 sulfur + 2 S-adenosyl-L-methionine = protein N6-(lipoyl)lysine + 2 L-methionine + 2 5'-deoxyadenosyl.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of 3'-phosphotyrosyl groups formed as covalent intermediates (in DNA backbone breakage) between DNA topoisomerase I and DNA.

BaiduTrans: MAP激酶酪氨酸/丝氨酸/苏氨酸磷酸酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: MAP kinase serine/threonine/tyrosine phosphate + H2O = MAP kinase serine/threonine/tyrosine + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: phosphomyosin + H2O = myosin + phosphate.
Binding to a myosin; myosins are any of a superfamily of molecular motor proteins that bind to actin and use the energy of ATP hydrolysis to generate force and movement along actin filaments.
Binding to a member of the class of TATA-binding proteins (TBP), including any of the TBP-related factors (TRFs).
Catalysis of the reaction: sphingosine + ATP = sphingosine 1-phosphate + ADP.
The action of a molecule that contributes to the structural integrity of the nuclear pore complex, a protein-lined channel in the nuclear envelope that allows the transfer of macromolecules.
Catalysis of the reaction: 6-O-phosphono-D-glucono-1,5-lactone + H(2)O = 6-phospho-D-gluconate + H(+).

BaiduTrans: S-甲基-5-硫代腺苷磷酸化酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 5'-methylthioadenosine + phosphate = adenine + 5-methylthio-D-ribose 1-phosphate.
Binding to a small nuclear RNA (snRNA).
Binding to a U6 small nuclear RNA (U6 snRNA).
Binding to a purine nucleotide, a compound consisting of a purine nucleoside esterified with (ortho)phosphate.
Catalysis of the cleavage of a 5' flap structure in DNA, but not other DNA structures; processes the 5' ends of Okazaki fragments in lagging strand DNA synthesis.
Catalysis of the reaction: a nucleoside diphosphate + H2O = a nucleoside monophosphate  + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: a nucleoside triphosphate + H2O = nucleoside diphosphate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + H2O = ADP + phosphate, in the presence of single-stranded DNA; drives the unwinding of a DNA helix.
Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-lipoyl-5'-AMP + L-lysyl-[lipoyl-carrier protein] = (R)-N6-lipoyl-L-lysyl-[lipoyl-carrier protein] + AMP + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the insertion of a dCMP residue opposite a template abasic site in DNA.
Catalysis of the movement of phospholipids from one membrane bilayer leaflet to the other, by an ATP-independent mechanism.

BaiduTrans: NAD依赖性组蛋白脱乙酰酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: histone N6-acetyl-L-lysine + H2O = histone L-lysine + acetate. This reaction requires the presence of NAD, and represents the removal of an acetyl group from a histone.
Catalysis of the reaction: tRNA-uracil + acceptor = tRNA-dihydrouridine + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction: 5-oxo-L-proline + ATP + 2 H(2)O = L-glutamate + ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a substrate by a catalytic mechanism that involves a catalytic triad consisting of a serine nucleophile that is activated by a proton relay involving an acidic residue (e.g. aspartate or glutamate) and a basic residue (usually histidine).

BaiduTrans: 磷脂酰肌醇N-乙酰氨基葡萄糖基转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + phosphatidylinositol = UDP + N-acetyl-D-glucosaminylphosphatidylinositol.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + diphthine + NH(4)(+) = ADP + diphthamide + H(+) + phosphate.

BaiduTrans: 蛋白质-L-组氨酸N-末端甲基转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-histidyl-[protein] + S-adenosyl-L-methionine = N(tele)-methyl-L-histidyl-[protein] + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-threonine = D-threonine.

description: protein C-terminal leucine carboxyl O-methyltransferase activity
BaiduTrans: 蛋白质C-末端亮氨酸羧基O-甲基转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + protein L-leucine = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + protein L-leucine methyl ester. This modification occurs only at the oxygen atoms of the free alpha carboxyl group of a leucine residue at the C-terminus of the protein.
Catalysis of the reaction: 4-hydroxybenzaldehyde + NAD+ + H2O = 4-hydroxybenzoate + NADH + H+.

BaiduTrans: 季戊四醇三硝酸还原酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: pentaerythritol trinitrate + NADPH = NADP+ + nitrate + pentaerythritol dinitrate.
Catalysis of the reaction: ethylnitronate + O(2) = acetaldehyde + nitrite.

BaiduTrans: S-甲酰谷胱甘肽水解酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: S-formylglutathione + H(2)O = formate + glutathione + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction: dodecyl sulfate + H2O = sulfate + H+ + 1-dodecanol.

BaiduTrans: 乙酰丙酮酸水解酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: acetylpyruvate + H(2)O = acetate + H(+) + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction: alkene-CoA + H2O = alcohol-CoA. Substrates are crotonoyl-CoA (producing 3-hydroxyacyl-CoA) and 2,3-didehydro-pimeloyl-CoA (producing 3-hydroxypimeloyl-CoA).
Catalysis of the reaction: urea = cyanamide + H(2)O.
Binding to a guanyl nucleotide, consisting of guanosine esterified with (ortho)phosphate.
Binding to GDP, guanosine 5'-diphosphate.

Catalysis of the removal of damaged bases by cleaving the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the target damaged DNA base and the deoxyribose sugar. The reaction releases a free base and leaves an apurinic/apyrimidinic (AP) site.

BaiduTrans: 脱氧尿嘧啶单加氧酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: protein N6-(4-aminobutyl)-L-lysine + donor-H2 + O2 = protein N6-((R)-4-amino-2-hydroxybutyl)-L-lysine + acceptor + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + D-ribulose = ADP + D-ribulose 5-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: acetoin + NAD+ = diacetyl + NADH + H+.

BaiduTrans: 蛋白质二硫还原酶（谷胱甘肽）活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2 glutathione + protein-disulfide = oxidized glutathione + protein-dithiol.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + D-mannose = ADP + D-mannose 6-phosphate.

BaiduTrans: 反式-2-烯醇基-CoA还原酶（NADPH）活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: acyl-CoA + NADP+ = trans-2,3-dehydroacyl-CoA + NADPH + H+.

BaiduTrans: 甲基乙二醛还原酶（NADH依赖性）活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-lactaldehyde + NAD+ = methylglyoxal + NADH + H+.

BaiduTrans: 3-羟酰基-[酰基载体蛋白]脱水酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: a (3R)-3-hydroxyacyl-[acyl-carrier protein] = H2O + a trans-delta2-enoyl-acyl-[acyl-carrier protein].
Catalysis of the reaction: methylglyoxal + H2O = D-lactate.
Catalysis of the transfer of a mannose residue to an oligosaccharide, forming a beta-(1->4) linkage.

BaiduTrans: 含核碱基的复合激酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP or GTP, to a nucleobase, nucleoside, nucleotide or polynucleotide substrate.
Modulates the activity of a kinase, an enzyme which catalyzes of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.
Binds to and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a kinase.
Binds to and increases the activity of a phosphatase, an enzyme which catalyzes of the removal of a phosphate group from a substrate molecule.
Binding to a centromere, a region of chromosome where the spindle fibers attach during mitosis and meiosis.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any non-peptide carbon-nitrogen bond in a cyclic amidine, a compound of the form R-C(=NH)-NH2, in a reaction that involves the opening of a ring.
Catalysis of the removal of an amino group from a substrate, producing a substituted or nonsubstituted ammonia (NH3/NH2R).

BaiduTrans: 蛋白质精氨酸N5甲基转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a methyl group from S-adenosyl-L-methionine to the delta-nitrogen atom of peptidyl-arginine residues. The reaction is S-adenosyl-L-methionine + [protein]-L-arginine = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + [protein]-N5-methyl-L-arginine.

BaiduTrans: 蛋白质半胱氨酸S-棕榈酰转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a palmitoyl (systematic name, hexadecanoyl) group to a sulfur atom on the cysteine of a protein molecule, in the reaction hexadecanoyl-CoA + L-cysteinyl-[protein] = CoA + S-hexadecanoyl-L-cysteinyl-[protein].
Catalysis of the covalent attachment of the ubiquitin-like protein Atg8 to substrate molecules; phosphatidylethanolamine is a known substrate.
Catalysis of the transfer of ATG12 from one protein to another via the reaction X-ATG12 + Y --> Y-ATG12 + X, where both X-ATG12 and Y-ATG12 are covalent linkages.
Catalysis of the activation of the small ubiquitin-related modifier APG12, through the formation of an ATP-dependent high-energy thiolester bond.
Catalysis of the activation of the small ubiquitin-related modifier APG8, through the formation of an ATP-dependent high-energy thiolester bond.
Catalysis of the initiation of the NEDD8 (RUB1) conjugation cascade.
An isopeptidase activity that cleaves ubiquitin or ubiquitin-like proteins (ULP; e.g. ATG8, ISG15, NEDD8, SUMO) from target proteins.
An isopeptidase activity that cleaves NEDD8 from a target protein to which it is conjugated.
A thiol-dependent isopeptidase activity that cleaves APG8 from a target protein to which it is conjugated.

BaiduTrans: 泛素样蛋白转移酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a ubiquitin-like from one protein to another via the reaction X-ULP + Y --> Y-ULP + X, where both X-ULP and Y-ULP are covalent linkages. ULP represents a ubiquitin-like protein.
Catalysis of the transfer of NEDD8 from one protein to another via the reaction X-NEDD8 + Y --> Y-NEDD8 + X, where both X-NEDD8 and Y-NEDD8 are covalent linkages.
Catalysis of the transfer of SUMO from one protein to another via the reaction X-SUMO + Y --> Y-SUMO + X, where both X-SUMO and Y-SUMO are covalent linkages.
Binding to oxygen (O2).

BaiduTrans: 天冬氨酸型内肽酶抑制剂活性
definition: Binds to and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of aspartic-type endopeptidases, enzymes that catalyze the hydrolysis of nonterminal peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain; the optimum reaction pH is below 5 due to an aspartic residue involved in the catalytic process.

BaiduTrans: ATP酶偶联阳离子跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: ATP + H2O + cation(out) = ADP + phosphate + cation(in).
Binding to a ribosomal RNA.
Modulates the activity of a protein kinase, an enzyme which phosphorylates a protein.
Binds to and modulates the activity of a protein phosphatase, an enzyme which catalyzes of the removal of a phosphate group from a protein substrate molecule.
Binding to an enzyme, a protein with catalytic activity.
Binding to a kinase, any enzyme that catalyzes the transfer of a phosphate group.
Binding to a protein kinase, any enzyme that catalyzes the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a protein substrate.
Binding to a phosphatase.
Binding to a protein phosphatase.

BaiduTrans: 蛋白质结构域特异性结合
definition: Binding to a specific domain of a protein.
Binding to a syntaxin, a SNAP receptor involved in the docking of synaptic vesicles at the presynaptic zone of a synapse.

BaiduTrans: [丙酮酸脱氢酶（硫酰胺）]磷酸酶调节活性
definition: Binds to and modulates of the activity of [pyruvate dehydrogenase (lipoamide)] phosphatase.

description: cyclin-dependent protein kinase activating kinase activity
BaiduTrans: 细胞周期素依赖性蛋白激酶激活激酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + a protein = ADP + a phosphoprotein; increases the activity of a cyclin-dependent protein kinase (CDK).
Catalysis of the activation of the proteolytically processed small ubiquitin-related modifier SUMO, through the formation of an ATP-dependent high-energy thiolester bond.
Binding to a heme, a compound composed of iron complexed in a porphyrin (tetrapyrrole) ring.
Enables the transport of a potassium ion across a membrane via a narrow pore channel that is open even in an unstimulated or 'resting' state.
Enables the transfer of a substance, usually a specific substance or a group of related substances, from one side of a membrane to the other.

BaiduTrans: 无机阳离子跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Enables the transfer of inorganic cations from one side of a membrane to the other. Inorganic cations are atoms or small molecules with a positive charge that do not contain carbon in covalent linkage.

BaiduTrans: 低亲和力色氨酸跨膜转运蛋白活性
definition: Catalysis of the low-affinity transfer of L-tryptophan from one side of a membrane to the other. Tryptophan is 2-amino-3-(1H-indol-3-yl)propanoic acid. In low-affinity transport the transporter is able to bind the solute only if it is present at very high concentrations.
Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-malate + NAD+ = oxaloacetate + NADH + H+.
Binding to a manganese ion (Mn).

BaiduTrans: 信号受体复合物适配器活性
definition: The binding activity of a molecule that provides a physical support for the assembly of a multiprotein receptor signaling complex.
Binding to pyridoxal 5' phosphate, 3-hydroxy-5-(hydroxymethyl)-2-methyl4-pyridine carboxaldehyde 5' phosphate, the biologically active form of vitamin B6.
Binds to and modulates the activity of an enzyme.

Binding to a carbohydrate, which includes monosaccharides, oligosaccharides and polysaccharides as well as substances derived from monosaccharides by reduction of the carbonyl group (alditols), by oxidation of one or more hydroxy groups to afford the corresponding aldehydes, ketones, or carboxylic acids, or by replacement of one or more hydroxy group(s) by a hydrogen atom. Cyclitols are generally not regarded as carbohydrates.
Catalysis of the reaction: glycolate + NADP+ = glyoxylate + NADPH + H+.

BaiduTrans: 5-甲酰四氢叶酸环连接酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 5-formyltetrahydrofolate + ATP = 5,10-methenyltetrahydrofolate + ADP + H(+) + phosphate.
Binding to a clathrin heavy or light chain, the main components of the coat of coated vesicles and coated pits, and which also occurs in synaptic vesicles.

BaiduTrans: DNA聚合酶过程性因子活性

Catalysis of the synthesis of free D-serine from L-serine.
Binds to and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a peptidase, any enzyme that catalyzes the hydrolysis peptide bonds.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-kynurenine + H2O = anthranilate + L-alanine.
Binding to a small nucleolar RNA.
The action of a molecule that contributes to the structural integrity of chromatin.
Binding to a Hsp70 protein, heat shock proteins around 70kDa in size.
Binding to cAMP, the nucleotide cyclic AMP (adenosine 3',5'-cyclophosphate).
Catalysis of the interconversion of arsenate and arsenite.
Binding to a U1 small nuclear RNA (U1 snRNA).
Binding to a U2 small nuclear RNA (U2 snRNA).
Binding to a U4 small nuclear RNA (U4 snRNA).
Binding to a U5 small nuclear RNA (U5 snRNA).
Binding to a pre-mRNA 5' splice site sequence.
Binding to a pre-mRNA 3' splice site sequence.

Binds to and modulates the activity of a GTPase.
Catalysis of the transfer of a methyl group from a donor to the C5 atom of the uridine residue at position 54 in a tRNA molecule.

Binding to a potassium ion (K+).
Binding to thiamine (vitamin B1), a water soluble vitamin present in fresh vegetables and meats, especially liver.
Binding to thiamine pyrophosphate, the diphosphoric ester of thiamine. Acts as a coenzyme of several (de)carboxylases, transketolases, and alpha-oxoacid dehydrogenases.
Binding to a double-stranded DNA region containing one or more mismatches.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-cysteine + [enzyme]-cysteine = L-alanine + [enzyme]-S-sulfanylcysteine.
Binding to a heat shock protein, a protein synthesized or activated in response to heat shock.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-serine + NADP(+) = L-alpha-formylglycine + 2 H(+) + NADPH.

BaiduTrans: 组蛋白甲基转移酶活性（H3-K79特异性）
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + histone H3 L-lysine (position 79) = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + histone H3 N6-methyl-L-lysine (position 79). This reaction is the addition of a methyl group onto lysine at position 79 of the histone H3 protein.
Binding to phosphopantetheine, the vitamin pantetheine 4'-(dihydrogen phosphate).
Binding to a phosphatidylcholine, a glycophospholipid in which a phosphatidyl group is esterified to the hydroxyl group of choline.
Binding to a small monomeric GTPase.
Binding to a translation initiation factor, any polypeptide factor involved in the initiation of ribosome-mediated translation.
Binding to eukaryotic initiation factor 4G, a polypeptide factor involved in the initiation of ribosome-mediated translation.

A molecular function exhibited by a protein that is covalently attached (AKA tagged or conjugated) to another protein where it acts as a marker, recognized by the cellular apparatus to target the tagged protein for some cellular process such as modification, sequestration, transport or degradation.
Binding to lipoic acid, 1,2-dithiolane-3-pentanoic acid.
Binding to L-ascorbic acid, (2R)-2-[(1S)-1,2-dihydroxyethyl]-4-hydroxy-5-oxo-2,5-dihydrofuran-3-olate; L-ascorbic acid is vitamin C and has co-factor and anti-oxidant activities in many species.

description: mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase kinase binding
BaiduTrans: 丝裂原活化蛋白激酶结合

Binding to DNA that is assembled into chromatin.
Binding to a nucleosome, a complex comprised of DNA wound around a multisubunit core and associated proteins, which forms the primary packing unit of DNA into higher order structures.
Binding to the DNA portion of a nucleosome.

BaiduTrans: 肽基脯氨酸双加氧酶活性

Binding to a G-protein beta subunit.
Binding to a G-protein gamma subunit.

BaiduTrans: 中链脂肪酸辅酶A连接酶活性

Binding to a light chain of a myosin complex.
Binding to a light chain of a myosin II complex.
Binding to the tail region of a myosin II heavy chain.
Binding to a heavy chain of a myosin complex.
Binding to a heavy chain of a myosin II complex.

Binding to a clathrin heavy chain.
Binding to a clathrin light chain.

Binding to a SAM (Sterile Alpha Motif) domain, which is a 70-amino acid protein sequence that participates in protein-protein, protein-lipid, and protein-RNA interactions and is conserved from lower to higher eukaryotes.
Binding to an alkylated residue in DNA.
Binding to a double-stranded DNA region containing an insertion or a deletion.

BaiduTrans: 鸟嘌呤/胸腺嘧啶空气结合

definition: Enables the transfer of riboflavin from one side of a membrane to the other. Riboflavin (vitamin B2) is a water-soluble B-complex vitamin, converted in the cell to FMN and FAD, cofactors required for the function of flavoproteins.
Binding to phosphatidylinositol-3-phosphate, a derivative of phosphatidylinositol in which the inositol ring is phosphorylated at the 3' position.
Binding to a MutSalpha mismatch repair complex.
Catalysis of the reaction: n-alkanal + NAD(P)+ = alk-2-enal + NAD(P)H + H+.

BaiduTrans: 麦芽糖α-葡萄糖苷酶活性

Catalysis of the removal of a methyl group from a histone.

BaiduTrans: 组蛋白H3-甲基赖氨酸-4去甲基化酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the removal of a methyl group from a modified lysine residue at position 4 of the histone H3 protein.

BaiduTrans: 组蛋白H3-甲基赖氨酸-9去甲基化酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the removal of a methyl group from a modified lysine residue at position 9 of the histone H3 protein.
Catalysis of the reaction: peroxiredoxin-(S-hydroxy-S-oxocysteine) + ATP + 2 R-SH = peroxiredoxin-(S-hydroxycysteine) + ADP + phosphate + R-S-S-R.
Binding to a ribonucleoside, a compound consisting of a purine or pyrimidine nitrogenous base linked to ribose.
Binding to an adenyl ribonucleotide, any compound consisting of adenosine esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the ribose moiety.
Binding to a GTPase activating protein.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-xylitol + NADP+ = D-xylose + NADPH + H+.

Binding to a sterol, a steroid containing a hydroxy group in the 3 position, closely related to cholestan-3-ol.
Binds transmembrane domain-containing proteins and mediates their integration into a membrane.

Binding to a FFAT motif, a short motif containing diphenylalanine in an acidic tract that targets proteins to the cytosolic surface of the ER and to the nuclear membrane by binding directly to members of the VAP (VAMP-associated protein) protein family.

BaiduTrans: 糖脂1,6-α-甘露基转移酶活性

BaiduTrans: 蛋白质赖氨酸脱乙酰酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + N6-acetyl-L-lysyl-[protein] = acetate + L-lysyl-[protein].
An activity that facilitates the formation of a complementary double-stranded RNA molecule.
Unwinding of a DNA/RNA duplex, i.e. a double helix in which a strand of DNA pairs with a complementary strand of RNA, driven by ATP hydrolysis.
Unwinding of a DNA/RNA duplex in the 5' to 3' direction, driven by ATP hydrolysis.

BaiduTrans: DNA 5'-腺苷一磷酸水解酶活性

BaiduTrans: L-甲硫氨酸-（R）-S-氧化物还原酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-methionine + thioredoxin disulfide + H2O = L-methionine (R)-S-oxide + thioredoxin.

Catalysis of the reaction: tryptophan + O2 = N-formylkynurenine. The product of the reaction depends on the substrate; D-tryptophan produces N-formyl-D-kynurenine, and L-tryptophan produces N-formyl-L-kynurenine.

BaiduTrans: 脂酰（辛酰基）转移酶活性

BaiduTrans: 葡聚糖1,4-α-麦芽三糖水解酶活性
definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1->4)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in amylaceous polysaccharides, to remove successive maltotriose residues from the non-reducing chain ends.

Catalysis of the reaction: [eIF5A-precursor]-lysine + spermidine = [eIF5A-precursor]-deoxyhypusine + propane-1,3-diamine. Four sub-reactions have been identified,in which the intermediates remain tightly associated with the enzyme: spermidine + NAD+ = dehydrospermidine + NADH; dehydrospermidine + [enzyme]-lysine = N-(4-aminobutylidene)-[enzyme]-lysine + propane-1,3-diamine; N-(4-aminobutylidene)-[enzyme]-lysine + [eIF5A-precursor]-lysine = N-(4-aminobutylidene)-[eIF5A-precursor]-lysine + [enzyme]-lysine; N-(4-aminobutylidene)-[eIF5A-precursor]-lysine + NADH + H+ = [eIF5A-precursor]-deoxyhypusine + NAD+.

BaiduTrans: 8-氧代-7,8-二氢鸟嘌呤DNA N-糖苷酶活性

Facilitates the displacement of one strand of an RNA-RNA duplex and its replacement with a different strand of higher complementarity.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of an acetyl group or groups from an acetylated sterol.
Catalysis of the acetylation of an amino acid residue of a peptide or protein, according to the reaction: acetyl-CoA + peptide = CoA + N-acetylpeptide.

BaiduTrans: 蛋白激酶A催化亚单位结合
definition: Binding to one or both of the catalytic subunits of protein kinase A.
Interacting with the mitochondrial promoter DNA to modulate transcription by the mitochondrial RNA polymerase.

BaiduTrans: 乙醇O-辛烷酰转移酶活性

Catalysis of the reaction: a carboxylic ester + H2O = an alcohol + a carboxylic anion, where the carboxylic chain has 8 or fewer carbon atoms.
Catalysis of the removal of a 5' terminal pyrophosphate from the 5'-triphosphate end of an RNA, leaving a 5'-monophosphate end.

Isoenergetic transfer of ubiquitin from one protein to an existing ubiquitin chain via the reaction X-ubiquitin + Y-ubiquitin -> Y-ubiquitin-ubiquitin + X, where both the X-ubiquitin and Y-ubiquitin-ubiquitin linkages are thioester bonds between the C-terminal glycine of ubiquitin and a sulfhydryl side group of a cysteine residue.
Unwinding of an RNA helix in the 3' to 5' direction, driven by ATP hydrolysis.

BaiduTrans: 磷脂酰甘油磷脂酶C活性
definition: Catalysis of the reaction: a phosphatidylglycerol + H2O = 1,2-diacylglycerol + glycerol 3-phosphate.
Binding to a U3 small nucleolar RNA.
